From a5c5ebf1e99e76ca851e920d65d4501daa89f083 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 10:58:13 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate dictionary hot paths with type init

Production telemetry identified the dictionary hot path split across automatic
overlay groups d5 and d6 as a source of repeated startup transitions. Merge the
exact measured 43-function dictionary set into explicit type-init group 7.
Post-link residency verification enforces that the final group fits the
90,112-byte slot.

Keep PyObject_IS_GC and _Py_NewReference Hub-resident because they are tiny,
transition-heavy helpers. On P2, give _PyDict_NotifyEvent one external group-7
implementation so its header users cannot emit duplicate public overlay stubs;
retain the static inline implementation elsewhere.
